# Normalize line endings across Windows / Linux / macOS checkouts.
# Without this, a Windows contributor with core.autocrlf=true can land
# CRLF in the index and break the bash scripts on Linux/macOS — bash
# treats \r as part of the command and fails with cryptic errors.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-suspenders for the highest-stakes case: shell scripts MUST be
# LF. Listed explicitly so the policy is visible to future contributors.
*.sh text eol=lf
